#Text=Jimmie Johnson wins seventh NASCAR Cup Series championship
#Text=Wednesday , November 23 , 2016
#Text=Jimmie Johnson in 2015
#Text=Image : Sarah Stierch .
#Text=On Sunday , Jimmie Johnson of Hendrick Motorsports won the 2016 Ford EcoBoost 400 at the Homestead-Miami Speedway and his seventh NASCAR Sprint Cup Series championship .
#Text=The title tied him with Richard Petty and Dale Earnhardt for the most in Cup Series history .
#Text=Although he qualified 14th , a ruling of illegal modifications to his car required him to start the race at the back of the field of 40 cars .
#Text=Meanwhile , fellow Chase for the Sprint Cup contenders Kyle Busch , Carl Edwards and Joey Logano qualified 9th , 10th and 13th , respectively .
#Text=Pole position winner Kevin Harvick led the first 31 laps ; Kyle Larson led the race high of 132 laps .
#Text=Despite his last-place start , Johnson was able to reach the top five in less than 50 laps .
#Text=However , Johnson remained behind his three championship rivals .
#Text=The race featured seven caution periods , six different leaders and 20 lead changes .
#Text=The first caution came when Ryan Blaney hit the wall on lap 28 ; he would be involved in another caution on lap 208 .
#Text=Jeffrey Earnhardt spun on lap 81 , while the third caution of the night came for debris on lap 172 .
#Text=On a restart with ten laps to go , Edwards collided with Logano while attempting to block him .
#Text=The resulting crash collected Brad Keselowski , Ryan Newman , Kasey Kahne , Ty Dillon , Chase Elliott , Regan Smith and Martin Truex Jr. , whose car caught fire after hitting Keselowski .
#Text=Logano received minimal damage in the contact with Edwards and was able to continue .
#Text=With less than four laps left , Ricky Stenhouse Jr. hit the wall , resulting in an overtime finish , which extended the race length to 268 laps .
#Text=Johnson took the lead from Larson with three laps to go and held on to win his 80th Cup race and the championship .
#Text=Johnson commented , " It 's just beyond words [ ... ]
